Ben,


I&#39;m glad you found this site and are enjoying it.  I started the site a 
number of years ago.  At that time, I was cautioned against it, because 
one person in particular was concerned that it would divide the 
advocates of a new English alphabet, as promoted by G. B. Shaw and and 
brought to reality by Kingsley Read, and would be a negative influence 
overall.


I did not see competition with Shawscript as a problem.  I have never 
regretted starting the site.  We have a large group of members who, I am 
confident, use the alphabet in their lives to advantage.


I will say that I have personally found the alphabet very useful over 
the last 45 years or so.


Enjoy!




Paige Gabhart




